Description: Beerock Studios makes products that push the boundaries of multiplayer gaming
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: We build platforms and tools that push the boundaries of multiplayer gaming. To date, over 12 million like-minded gamers discover, connect and team up for more meaningful multiplayer experiences using our products. Our latest, For The Win - FTW.in,  launched summer 2017, unifies all of our existing LFG (Looking for Group) products into a single experience.  Beerock was founded in 2014 by Brock Busby, who set out to solve a key problem for gamers today: how to play team-based multiplayer games when your friends are not around. Brock had experienced this problem first-hand through the hit game, Destiny, which required expertly coordinated teamwork in order to beat its hardest content.  The studio's first product, DestinyLFG.com, enabled like-minded gamers to team-up before a match to have the best  gaming experience. According to feedback from our fans, DestinyLFG extended the playability of the original Destiny by an average of six months.  Following the success of DestinyLFG.com, Beerock launched several LFG sites to support players of Overwatch, Call of Duty, The Division, and GTA V. Then in 2017, the studio launched the FTW.in product, and LFG system to support all games. To date, FTW.in has over 100,000 registered users and growing!

Wanting to have more control over the outcome of their investments and see them up close eventually caused them to move away from the stock market and focus more on real estate as investors and lenders. After a few years as real estate lenders and brokers, they decided to focus on the service side of the industry. By 2010, Del Toro was providing document preparation and loan servicing to over 1,000 people, causing business to grow over 20% annually since that time. The reason for the steady growth was due to both the quality of Del Toro clients and the passionate and professional staff. Del Toro has a culture that revolves around constant personal and professional development. While others claim to be great, Del Toro promises to be different. Description: Platte River Gathering System provides gathering for crude oil production in the heart of the prolific.
Full Description: The Platte River Pipeline Gathering System will originate at various wellhead and truck injection stations in Weld County, Colorado and terminate at the Rimrock Midstream crude oil terminal near Lucerne, Colorado.  The Platte River System will provide critical crude oil gathering capacity for producers in the Denver-Julesburg Basin.  As proposed, the system will be capable of receiving and transporting in excess of 130,000 barrels per day for delivery into Rimrock’s Lucerne West Station, located adjacent to the Lucerne origination point for the Grand Mesa/Saddlehorn Pipeline, which offers delivery to the Cushing, Oklahoma crude oil hub.  The Platte River System not only supports the continued growth of crude oil production in the area, but does so in a cost-effective and environmentally responsible way by reducing the current utilization of rail and truck transportation in many populated municipalities in Northern Colorado.

Description: Neutral Path Communications is a network neutral provider of fiber transport solutions.
Full Description: Neutral Path was born out of broadband service provider demand for a simple and route mile efficient means to fill the growing need for fiber connectivity to key points in the Midwest. While many parts of this region have  significant fiber resources, in many cases these facilities are underutilized because they are often difficult to identify, source, connect and ultimately provide an efficient, single source solution to a carrier’s connectivity needs. Neutral Path provides that single source solution. We design our fiber network to optimize connections to key carrier aggregation points, enabling cost saving public and private peering and access to low cost upstream Internet providers. In addition, we establish wholesale relationships with existing fiber owner/operators with fiber capacity to last mile destinations off of our primary long haul path, thus making it easier for customers to reach these key aggregation points, while creating new revenue opportunities for our customer partners with this excess fiber.

Description: Cathy Locke is the custom chocolatier behind the magic of Cathy’s Fine Chocolate.
Full Description: Cathy Locke is the custom chocolatier behind the magic of Cathy’s Fine Chocolate. The company has been pleasing Texas chocolate lovers with unique handmade Belgian chocolate since 2009. Cathy’s goal to become a unique, custom chocolatier came from a lifelong desire to learn how to combine the world of chocolates and her love for Texas wines — and an ongoing fascination with viniculture. Once Cathy made the decision to become a chocolatier, she embarked upon a year of intense self-study, devouring recipe books, doing on-line searches and meeting with chefs to learn the skills she needed to perfect her craft. After several years of refining her recipes and patiently tweaking her formulas, she has been able to successfully customize chocolate truffles exclusively for Texas wineries and other clients who seek out the best in chocolate for their events or to serve with their products. Today, in addition to producing a number of other products, Cathy and her small staff turn out several thousand chocolate truffles a week, every single one made by hand! And now Cathy is proud to announce her affiliation with Go Texan!
